await page.click('#submit');
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you test partial provisioning failures?
- How ensure no cross-tenant data leakage in logs?

## Why This Is Asked

Tests in privacy-preserving analytics must guarantee erasure across all data stores, including caches, materialized views, and backups, while maintaining accurate audit trails for compliance.

## Key Concepts
- DSAR data erasure across microservices
- Event sourcing and tombstone propagation
- Soft vs hard deletes and retention windows
- Cross-region replication and data consistency
- Audit logs and backups scrub policy

## Code Example

```javascript
// Pseudo-test outline for DSAR flow
test('DSAR end-to-end erasure', async () => {
  seedTestUser();
  ingestEvents();
  triggerDSAR();
  await expect(dataRemovedFromPrimaryDB()).toBe(true);
  await expect(eventStoreHasDeletion()).toBe(true);
  await expect(cacheInvalidated()).toBe(true);
  await expect(auditLogsContain('DSAR')).toBe(true);
});
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you validate that backups are scrubbed after the retention window without impacting restore capabilities?
- What observability signals would you add to detect DSAR failures in a multi-region deployment?

