## Why This Is Asked
Tests across multiple regions and orchestration layers are common in cloud-native, multi-tenant platforms. This checks data isolation, regional consistency, rollback safety, and observability.

## Key Concepts
- Multi-region provisioning and consistency
- Test data isolation and tenant-scoped seeds
- Idempotent retries and rollback guarantees
- Chaos/traffic shaping for regional failover
- Observability with distributed tracing

## Code Example
```javascript
// Pseudo test sketch (Playwright/Cypress style)
test('onboard tenant end-to-end', async () => {
  const tenantId = `tn-${Date.now()}`;
  await signupTenant(tenantId);
  await provisionRegions(tenantId, ['us-east', 'eu-west', 'ap-south']);
  await configureIAM(tenantId, 'default-role');
  await activateBillingTrial(tenantId, 30);
  await assertRegionalConvergence(tenantId, 120000);
  await retryWithIdempotency(tenantId);
  await verifyRollbackOnFailure(tenantId);
  const trace = await fetchTrace(tenantId);
  expect(trace).toBeDefined();
});
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you measure and mitigate flaky tests in this setup?
- What telemetry and retries would you implement to differentiate real failures from transient regional outages?
